Program: Discovery
Title: Ancient Olympics - getting ready
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryq8
Last Broadcast Date: 07 July 2004
The preparations made by athletes and authorities taking part in the ancient olympics. A month before the games began a truce was declared, so athletes and spectators could travel safely to Olympia. Only men were allowed to take part in the games which were held in honour of the Greek god Zeus.